s:1242:"<p dir="ltr"><strong><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Course Completion Requirements: Introduction to Logic and Critical Thinking</span><br /></strong></p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">To complete the Introduction to Logic and Critical Thinking course, you need to:</p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ol><li><strong>Complete All Modules:</strong> Successfully finish each module, covering key topics such as logical reasoning, argument structure, fallacies, and critical analysis.</li><li><strong>Pass Quizzes and Assessments: </strong>Achieve a passing score on all quizzes and assessments to demonstrate your understanding of logical concepts and critical thinking skills.</li><li><strong>Participate in Discussions:</strong>Â Engage in Module chats discussions and activities to apply your knowledge and interact with peers.</li><li><strong>Achieve a Minimum Grade:</strong> Attain the minimum grade set to ensure a solid grasp of logic and critical thinking fundamentals.</li></ol><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">Upon meeting these requirements, you will have demonstrated a strong ability to think logically and critically, equipping you with valuable skills for analyzing and evaluating information effectively.</p>";